What is the variance of the minority class¶

In [13]:
from imblearn.over_sampling import SMOTE
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
minority_class = new_df[new_df['Class'] == 1]
majority_class = new_df[new_df['Class'] == 0]
variance_minority = minority_class.var()
mean_min = [x for x in variance_minority]
average_min = sum(mean_min) / len(mean_min)

variance_majority = majority_class.var()
mean_maj = [x for x in variance_majority]
average_maj = sum(mean_maj) / len(mean_maj)
X = new_df.drop(columns='Class')
y = new_df['Class']
smote = SMOTE(random_state=42)
X_resampled, y_resampled = smote.fit_resample(X, y)
smote_df = X_resampled.copy()
smote_df['Class'] = y_resampled
smote_minority_class = smote_df[smote_df['Class'] == 1]
variance_smote_minority = smote_minority_class.var()
mean_smote_min = [x for x in variance_smote_minority]
average_smote_min = sum(mean_smote_min) / len(mean_smote_min)
labels = ['Original Minority Class', 'Original Majority Class', 'SMOTE Minority Class']
averages = [average_min, average_maj, average_smote_min]

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar(labels, averages, color=['red', 'blue', 'green'])
plt.title('Average Variance of Features by Class')
plt.ylabel('Average Variance')
plt.xticks(rotation=15)
plt.show()

In [15]:
from imblearn.combine import SMOTETomek
from imblearn.pipeline import Pipeline as ImbPipeline
from sklearn.metrics import precision_score, recall_score, f1_score, precision_recall_curve, auc
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split, StratifiedKFold

def evaluate_with_scenarios(model, X, y):
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(
        X, y, test_size=0.2, stratify=y, random_state=42
    )
    
    # Define cross-validation strategy
    skf = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=5, shuffle=True, random_state=42)

    # Scenario 1: Without SMOTE (Original Data)
    print("Scenario 1: Without SMOTE (Original Data)")
    no_smote_pipeline = ImbPipeline([
        ('classifier', model)
    ])
    
    precision_no_smote = []
    recall_no_smote = []
    f1_no_smote = []
    y_true_no_smote = []
    y_scores_no_smote = []

    for train_idx, val_idx in skf.split(X_train, y_train):
        X_train_fold, X_val_fold = X_train.iloc[train_idx], X_train.iloc[val_idx]
        y_train_fold, y_val_fold = y_train.iloc[train_idx], y_train.iloc[val_idx]
        
        no_smote_pipeline.fit(X_train_fold, y_train_fold)
        y_pred_fold = no_smote_pipeline.predict(X_val_fold)
        y_score_fold = no_smote_pipeline.predict_proba(X_val_fold)[:, 1]

        precision_no_smote.append(precision_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold))
        recall_no_smote.append(recall_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold))
        f1_no_smote.append(f1_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold))

        y_true_no_smote.extend(y_val_fold)
        y_scores_no_smote.extend(y_score_fold)

    mean_precision_no_smote = np.mean(precision_no_smote)
    mean_recall_no_smote = np.mean(recall_no_smote)
    mean_f1_no_smote = np.mean(f1_no_smote)
    std_recall_no_smote = np.std(recall_no_smote)

    print(f"Mean Precision (Without SMOTE): {mean_precision_no_smote:.2f}")
    print(f"Mean Recall (Without SMOTE): {mean_recall_no_smote:.2f} | Std: {std_recall_no_smote:.2f}")
    print(f"Mean F1 Score (Without SMOTE): {mean_f1_no_smote:.2f}")
    
    # Plot AUPRC for Scenario 1
    precision, recall, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_true_no_smote, y_scores_no_smote)
    auc_prc_no_smote = auc(recall, precision)
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
    plt.plot(recall, precision, color='blue', label=f'Without SMOTE (AUPRC = {auc_prc_no_smote:.3f})')

    # Scenario 2: With SMOTE (Oversampled Data)
    print("\nScenario 2: With SMOTE (Oversampled Data)")
    smote_pipeline = ImbPipeline([
        ('smote', SMOTE(sampling_strategy=0.5,random_state=42)),
        ('classifier', model)
    ])

    precision_smote = []
    recall_smote = []
    f1_smote = []
    y_true_smote = []
    y_scores_smote = []

    for train_idx, val_idx in skf.split(X_train, y_train):
        X_train_fold, X_val_fold = X_train.iloc[train_idx], X_train.iloc[val_idx]
        y_train_fold, y_val_fold = y_train.iloc[train_idx], y_train.iloc[val_idx]

        smote_pipeline.fit(X_train_fold, y_train_fold)
        y_pred_fold = smote_pipeline.predict(X_val_fold)
        y_score_fold = smote_pipeline.predict_proba(X_val_fold)[:, 1]

        precision_smote.append(precision_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold))
        recall_smote.append(recall_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold))
        f1_smote.append(f1_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold))

        y_true_smote.extend(y_val_fold)
        y_scores_smote.extend(y_score_fold)

    mean_precision_smote = np.mean(precision_smote)
    mean_recall_smote = np.mean(recall_smote)
    mean_f1_smote = np.mean(f1_smote)
    std_recall_smote = np.std(recall_smote)

    print(f"Mean Precision (With SMOTE): {mean_precision_smote:.2f}")
    print(f"Mean Recall (With SMOTE): {mean_recall_smote:.2f} | Std: {std_recall_smote:.2f}")
    print(f"Mean F1 Score (With SMOTE): {mean_f1_smote:.2f}")

    # Plot AUPRC for Scenario 2
    precision, recall, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_true_smote, y_scores_smote)
    auc_prc_smote = auc(recall, precision)
    plt.plot(recall, precision, color='green', label=f'With SMOTE (AUPRC = {auc_prc_smote:.3f})')

    # Scenario 3: With ADASYN (Oversampled Data)
    print("\nScenario 3: With ADASYN (Oversampled Data)")
    adasyn_pipeline = ImbPipeline([
        ('adasyn', ADASYN(random_state=42)),
        ('classifier', model)
    ])

    precision_adasyn = []
    recall_adasyn = []
    f1_adasyn = []
    y_true_adasyn = []
    y_scores_adasyn = []

    for train_idx, val_idx in skf.split(X_train, y_train):
        X_train_fold, X_val_fold = X_train.iloc[train_idx], X_train.iloc[val_idx]
        y_train_fold, y_val_fold = y_train.iloc[train_idx], y_train.iloc[val_idx]

        adasyn_pipeline.fit(X_train_fold, y_train_fold)
        y_pred_fold = adasyn_pipeline.predict(X_val_fold)
        y_score_fold = adasyn_pipeline.predict_proba(X_val_fold)[:, 1]

        precision_adasyn.append(precision_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold))
        recall_adasyn.append(recall_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold))
        f1_adasyn.append(f1_score(y_val_fold, y_pred_fold))

        y_true_adasyn.extend(y_val_fold)
        y_scores_adasyn.extend(y_score_fold)

    mean_precision_adasyn = np.mean(precision_adasyn)
    mean_recall_adasyn = np.mean(recall_adasyn)
    mean_f1_adasyn = np.mean(f1_adasyn)
    std_recall_adasyn = np.std(recall_adasyn)

    print(f"Mean Precision (With ADASYN): {mean_precision_adasyn:.2f}")
    print(f"Mean Recall (With ADASYN): {mean_recall_adasyn:.2f} | Std: {std_recall_adasyn:.2f}")
    print(f"Mean F1 Score (With ADASYN): {mean_f1_adasyn:.2f}")
    precision, recall, _ = precision_recall_curve(y_true_adasyn, y_scores_adasyn)
    auc_prc_adasyn = auc(recall, precision)
    plt.plot(recall, precision, color='red', label=f'With ADASYN (AUPRC = {auc_prc_adasyn:.3f})')
    plt.xlabel('Recall')
    plt.ylabel('Precision')
    plt.title('Precision-Recall Curve Comparison')
    plt.legend(loc="best")
    plt.show()
